00:00:09.530 --> 00:00:12.235 align:middle line:84%
and by the Witter Bynner
Foundation for Poetry.

00:00:12.235 --> 00:00:22.620 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.620 --> 00:00:26.590 align:middle line:84%
>>In the town of Konya
in central Turkey

00:00:26.590 --> 00:00:29.990 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of
the 13th century,

00:00:29.990 --> 00:00:32.560 align:middle line:84%
a prominent religious
scholar named

00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:37.270 align:middle line:84%
Jalal ad-Din Rumi was suddenly
separated from his teacher

00:00:37.270 --> 00:00:40.140 align:middle line:90%
and spiritual friend.

00:00:40.140 --> 00:00:43.620 align:middle line:84%
In his grief, he took hold of
a column and began turning.

00:00:43.620 --> 00:00:46.140 align:middle line:90%


00:00:46.140 --> 00:00:53.680 align:middle line:84%
Verses of poetry began pouring
out of him, remarkable poetry.

00:00:53.680 --> 00:00:57.940 align:middle line:84%
His students wrote
the words down.

00:00:57.940 --> 00:01:01.110 align:middle line:84%
700 years later,
Rumi's poetry is

00:01:01.110 --> 00:01:03.230 align:middle line:90%
being discovered in the West.

00:01:03.230 --> 00:01:07.521 align:middle line:84%
He is, in fact, the
bestselling poet in America.

00:01:07.521 --> 00:01:11.364 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:11.364 --> 00:01:27.620 align:middle line:90%


00:01:27.620 --> 00:01:31.220 align:middle line:90%
"Come to the orchard in spring.

00:01:31.220 --> 00:01:34.940 align:middle line:84%
There is light and wine and
sweethearts in the pomegranate

00:01:34.940 --> 00:01:37.520 align:middle line:90%
flowers.

00:01:37.520 --> 00:01:42.110 align:middle line:84%
If you do not come,
these do not matter.

00:01:42.110 --> 00:02:12.370 align:middle line:84%
If you do come,
these do not matter."

00:02:12.370 --> 00:02:16.450 align:middle line:84%
Rumi was born
September 30, 1207,

00:02:16.450 --> 00:02:19.360 align:middle line:84%
near Balkh, Afghanistan,
which was then

00:02:19.360 --> 00:02:22.770 align:middle line:90%
part of the Persian Empire.

00:02:22.770 --> 00:02:25.710 align:middle line:84%
When Rumi was still
a child, his family

00:02:25.710 --> 00:02:28.800 align:middle line:84%
was forced to flee the oncoming
armies of Genghis Khan.

00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:32.610 align:middle line:90%


00:02:32.610 --> 00:02:35.050 align:middle line:84%
After years of
travel, they settled

00:02:35.050 --> 00:02:39.470 align:middle line:84%
in Konya, Turkey, an important
stop on the Silk Road

00:02:39.470 --> 00:02:42.330 align:middle line:84%
and a meeting point
of many cultures--

00:02:42.330 --> 00:02:46.460 align:middle line:84%
Islamic, Judeo-Christian,
Hindu, and Buddhist.

00:02:46.460 --> 00:02:49.280 align:middle line:90%


00:02:49.280 --> 00:02:54.490 align:middle line:84%
Rumi's father became the head
of a Sufi learning community.

00:02:54.490 --> 00:02:57.510 align:middle line:84%
The Sufis are an
ancient spiritual order,

00:02:57.510 --> 00:03:02.050 align:middle line:84%
and according to many Sufis,
the essential truths of Sufism

00:03:02.050 --> 00:03:04.260 align:middle line:90%
exist in all religions.

00:03:04.260 --> 00:03:08.120 align:middle line:84%
>>The Sufis are
a remarkable band

00:03:08.120 --> 00:03:11.040 align:middle line:90%
in the history of religions.

00:03:11.040 --> 00:03:16.000 align:middle line:90%
They are the mystics of Islam.

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.660 align:middle line:10%
And as the mystics
of Islam, the Sufi

00:03:20.660 --> 00:03:23.340 align:middle line:10%
we can connect with,
because they're

00:03:23.340 --> 00:03:31.260 align:middle line:10%
talking about these wonderful,
sublime truths which

00:03:31.260 --> 00:03:37.570 align:middle line:10%
have a way of piercing directly
into the human heart, wherever

00:03:37.570 --> 00:03:38.960 align:middle line:10%
it is.

00:03:38.960 --> 00:03:42.950 align:middle line:84%
>>The Sufis used to
walk down several roads,

00:03:42.950 --> 00:03:45.600 align:middle line:84%
visiting with the Christians,
visiting with Islam,

00:03:45.600 --> 00:03:48.544 align:middle line:84%
visiting in all of the
great religions, really.

00:03:48.544 --> 00:03:50.460 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's part of
the nature of this kind

00:03:50.460 --> 00:03:52.250 align:middle line:90%
of fluid imagination.

00:03:52.250 --> 00:03:54.650 align:middle line:90%
It crosses boundaries.

00:03:54.650 --> 00:03:57.130 align:middle line:84%
It penetrates and
it even slips by,

00:03:57.130 --> 00:03:59.370 align:middle line:90%
and it works by way of humor.

00:03:59.370 --> 00:04:01.530 align:middle line:10%
It works by way of
stunning imagery.

00:04:01.530 --> 00:04:04.300 align:middle line:10%
It works in many
different ways as

00:04:04.300 --> 00:04:11.710 align:middle line:10%
if to keep bringing people
to some deep human well.

00:04:11.710 --> 00:04:14.630 align:middle line:84%
>>Upon his father's death,
Rumi became the head

00:04:14.630 --> 00:04:16.700 align:middle line:90%
of the learning community.

00:04:16.700 --> 00:04:19.070 align:middle line:84%
His life seems to have
been a fairly normal one

00:04:19.070 --> 00:04:21.430 align:middle line:84%
for a religious
scholar-- teaching,

00:04:21.430 --> 00:04:27.520 align:middle line:84%
meditating, helping the poor--
until the late fall of 1244,

00:04:27.520 --> 00:04:32.270 align:middle line:84%
when he met a stranger, a
wandering dervish, Shams

00:04:32.270 --> 00:04:34.000 align:middle line:90%
of Tabriz.

00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:41.630 align:middle line:84%
>>Rumi's genius was triggered
by an actual human being,

00:04:41.630 --> 00:04:46.650 align:middle line:84%
an encounter with this
mysterious figure,

00:04:46.650 --> 00:04:49.110 align:middle line:90%
Shams of Tabriz.

00:04:49.110 --> 00:04:53.730 align:middle line:10%
>>He was an intense,
fierce, mountain meditator.

00:04:53.730 --> 00:04:56.580 align:middle line:84%
Those kind of people, like
Thoreau magnified five times.

00:04:56.580 --> 00:04:59.400 align:middle line:84%
>>The connection
between Shams and Rumi

00:04:59.400 --> 00:05:05.670 align:middle line:84%
is one of the great
stories of learning

00:05:05.670 --> 00:05:07.990 align:middle line:84%
and what we nowaday
call mentoring.

00:05:07.990 --> 00:05:12.870 align:middle line:84%
But it's almost of an
order beyond what people

00:05:12.870 --> 00:05:15.520 align:middle line:84%
mean when they mean
to learn from someone,

00:05:15.520 --> 00:05:18.570 align:middle line:84%
because it means to almost--
what seemed to happen

00:05:18.570 --> 00:05:20.930 align:middle line:90%
was a sudden knowing.

00:05:20.930 --> 00:05:24.390 align:middle line:84%
>>One can see here
in Shams an older man

00:05:24.390 --> 00:05:28.410 align:middle line:84%
who is outside the orthodox
spiritual community who

00:05:28.410 --> 00:05:30.610 align:middle line:84%
comes in and helps
a younger man who

00:05:30.610 --> 00:05:34.280 align:middle line:84%
is deeply embedded in that
orthodox spiritual community.

00:05:34.280 --> 00:05:36.120 align:middle line:84%
And then there's a
kind of explosion.

00:05:36.120 --> 00:05:41.390 align:middle line:84%
>>What Rumi says, he says, he
was raw, then he got cooked.

00:05:41.390 --> 00:05:43.690 align:middle line:90%
And then he was burned.

00:05:43.690 --> 00:05:48.760 align:middle line:10%
And that means when his heart
only melted through his love

00:05:48.760 --> 00:05:54.330 align:middle line:10%
for Shams, that this
new experience enabled

00:05:54.330 --> 00:05:58.810 align:middle line:10%
him to understand what he
was talking about before.

00:05:58.810 --> 00:06:03.780 align:middle line:10%
>>And he took Rumi's
book knowledge and says,

00:06:03.780 --> 00:06:06.730 align:middle line:10%
now, you have to live what
you've been reading about.

00:06:06.730 --> 00:06:08.400 align:middle line:10%
Pushed all his books
into the fountain,

00:06:08.400 --> 00:06:10.050 align:middle line:10%
that's one story
of how they met.

00:06:10.050 --> 00:06:15.750 align:middle line:84%
And Rumi and he went off
into this practice called

00:06:15.750 --> 00:06:19.790 align:middle line:84%
conversation, or sohbet,
in which they disappeared

00:06:19.790 --> 00:06:23.780 align:middle line:84%
for evidently for
weeks at a time

00:06:23.780 --> 00:06:30.510 align:middle line:84%
in this conversation between
the personal and the deep self.

00:06:30.510 --> 00:06:33.865 align:middle line:84%
>>So this is the poem "I'm
Not Saying This Right,"

00:06:33.865 --> 00:06:35.740 align:middle line:84%
which, of course, might
mean that I might not

00:06:35.740 --> 00:06:37.200 align:middle line:90%
say the poem right.

00:06:37.200 --> 00:06:40.300 align:middle line:90%
So I'm not saying this right.

00:06:40.300 --> 00:06:43.140 align:middle line:84%
"You bind me, and I
tear away in a rage

00:06:43.140 --> 00:06:46.840 align:middle line:84%
to open out into air, a
round brightness, a candle

00:06:46.840 --> 00:06:50.040 align:middle line:90%
point, all reason, all love.

00:06:50.040 --> 00:06:52.750 align:middle line:84%
This confusing
joy is your doing,

00:06:52.750 --> 00:06:56.040 align:middle line:84%
this hangover your
tender thought.

00:06:56.040 --> 00:06:58.950 align:middle line:90%
You turn to look, I turn.

00:06:58.950 --> 00:07:00.910 align:middle line:90%
I'm not saying this right.

00:07:00.910 --> 00:07:04.590 align:middle line:84%
I'm a jailed crazy who
ties up spirit women.

00:07:04.590 --> 00:07:07.380 align:middle line:90%
No, I'm Solomon.

00:07:07.380 --> 00:07:09.370 align:middle line:90%
What goes, come back.

00:07:09.370 --> 00:07:11.140 align:middle line:90%
What goes comes back.

00:07:11.140 --> 00:07:12.650 align:middle line:90%
Come back.

00:07:12.650 --> 00:07:14.890 align:middle line:90%
We never left each other.

00:07:14.890 --> 00:07:18.020 align:middle line:84%
A disbeliever hides
all disbelief.

00:07:18.020 --> 00:07:20.500 align:middle line:90%
But I will say his secret now.

00:07:20.500 --> 00:07:23.320 align:middle line:84%
More and more awake,
getting up at night,

00:07:23.320 --> 00:07:26.430 align:middle line:84%
spinning and falling
in love with Shams,

00:07:26.430 --> 00:07:29.580 align:middle line:84%
falling with love for Shams,
spinning and spinning.

00:07:29.580 --> 00:07:31.610 align:middle line:90%
Falling in love with Shams.

00:07:31.610 --> 00:07:33.180 align:middle line:90%
Falling with love for Shams.

00:07:33.180 --> 00:07:36.620 align:middle line:90%
Falling with love for Shams."

00:07:36.620 --> 00:07:40.530 align:middle line:84%
>>And so Rumi became a poet
then, became a real poet,

00:07:40.530 --> 00:07:41.860 align:middle line:90%
became infused.

00:07:41.860 --> 00:07:44.330 align:middle line:90%
The whole spirit came into him.

00:07:44.330 --> 00:07:49.580 align:middle line:84%
And so that's one of the great
love affairs of the world,

00:07:49.580 --> 00:07:51.790 align:middle line:90%
the one between Shams and Rumi.

00:07:51.790 --> 00:07:54.490 align:middle line:84%
And they loved each
other, not sexually,

00:07:54.490 --> 00:07:57.210 align:middle line:84%
but they loved each
other in the heart.

00:07:57.210 --> 00:07:59.930 align:middle line:84%
>>Why does it impress
people so much?

00:07:59.930 --> 00:08:03.452 align:middle line:84%
Because it's a love
that is beyond gender,

00:08:03.452 --> 00:08:07.770 align:middle line:84%
beyond age, beyond
sex, beyond species.

00:08:07.770 --> 00:08:09.950 align:middle line:90%
It is the essence of love.

00:08:09.950 --> 00:08:18.420 align:middle line:10%
>>Two oceans met each other
in the force of love of God,

00:08:18.420 --> 00:08:21.980 align:middle line:10%
because the earth
has many oceans.

00:08:21.980 --> 00:08:23.880 align:middle line:90%
All the time, they meet.

00:08:23.880 --> 00:08:31.240 align:middle line:84%
And ones happened to meet in
the land of Konya, Turkey,

00:08:31.240 --> 00:08:32.760 align:middle line:90%
700 years ago.

00:08:32.760 --> 00:08:43.460 align:middle line:90%


00:08:43.460 --> 00:08:48.648 align:middle line:84%
>>"When you feel your lips
becoming infinite and sweet

00:08:48.648 --> 00:09:03.701 align:middle line:84%
like a moon in a sky, when you
feel that spaciousness inside,

00:09:03.701 --> 00:09:08.148 align:middle line:84%
Shams of Tabriz
will be there, too.

00:09:08.148 --> 00:09:22.120 align:middle line:90%


00:09:22.120 --> 00:09:23.540 align:middle line:90%
Something opens our wings.

00:09:23.540 --> 00:09:29.600 align:middle line:90%


00:09:29.600 --> 00:09:33.441 align:middle line:84%
Something makes boredom
and hurt disappear.

00:09:33.441 --> 00:09:37.770 align:middle line:90%


00:09:37.770 --> 00:09:41.310 align:middle line:84%
Someone fills the
cup in front of us.

00:09:41.310 --> 00:09:46.050 align:middle line:90%


00:09:46.050 --> 00:09:55.780 align:middle line:90%
We taste only sacredness."

00:09:55.780 --> 00:09:59.150 align:middle line:10%
>>The relationship
between Rumi and Shams

00:09:59.150 --> 00:10:04.030 align:middle line:10%
is actually a reminder to us
that all relationships have

00:10:04.030 --> 00:10:09.620 align:middle line:10%
that potential and that
when we fall in love,

00:10:09.620 --> 00:10:17.250 align:middle line:10%
then we actually are entering a
spiritual domain of awareness.

00:10:17.250 --> 00:10:19.510 align:middle line:90%
Romantic lovers are confused.

00:10:19.510 --> 00:10:22.990 align:middle line:84%
That's a very spiritual
state, to be confused.

00:10:22.990 --> 00:10:24.410 align:middle line:90%
Rumi says himself.

00:10:24.410 --> 00:10:29.540 align:middle line:84%
He says, label me and
define me, and you'll

00:10:29.540 --> 00:10:32.540 align:middle line:90%
starve yourself of yourself.

00:10:32.540 --> 00:10:35.160 align:middle line:84%
Nail me down in a
box with cold words,

00:10:35.160 --> 00:10:38.250 align:middle line:84%
and that box will
be your coffin.

00:10:38.250 --> 00:10:40.210 align:middle line:90%
Because I don't know who I am.

00:10:40.210 --> 00:10:43.590 align:middle line:84%
I'm in astounding,
lucid confusion.

00:10:43.590 --> 00:10:46.050 align:middle line:90%
That's the state of love.

00:10:46.050 --> 00:10:49.680 align:middle line:84%
>>There was a lot of jealousy
among Rumi's students

00:10:49.680 --> 00:10:51.620 align:middle line:90%
over this.

00:10:51.620 --> 00:10:55.090 align:middle line:84%
Jealousy is one of the main
impulses in the human race,

00:10:55.090 --> 00:10:57.020 align:middle line:90%
you know.

00:10:57.020 --> 00:10:58.670 align:middle line:84%
So no one knows
exactly the truth,

00:10:58.670 --> 00:11:02.420 align:middle line:84%
but some feel that what happened
is that the students killed

00:11:02.420 --> 00:11:06.270 align:middle line:90%
Shams, hid the body.

00:11:06.270 --> 00:11:07.960 align:middle line:84%
Rumi then went out
in the backyard,

00:11:07.960 --> 00:11:09.580 align:middle line:90%
and there was a pole there.

00:11:09.580 --> 00:11:12.170 align:middle line:84%
And in his grief, he kept
going round and round

00:11:12.170 --> 00:11:15.930 align:middle line:84%
and round and round the pole,
and this is the beginning

00:11:15.930 --> 00:11:17.709 align:middle line:90%
of the whirling dervishes.

00:11:17.709 --> 00:11:19.250 align:middle line:84%
Well, it was done
out of grief, which

00:11:19.250 --> 00:11:21.120 align:middle line:90%
is terrifically interesting.

00:11:21.120 --> 00:11:22.980 align:middle line:84%
That's how all that
great poetry started,

00:11:22.980 --> 00:11:27.510 align:middle line:84%
was in grief, the thing
that we avoid the most, hmm?

00:11:27.510 --> 00:11:29.970 align:middle line:84%
And in that time, he would
begin to speak the lines,

00:11:29.970 --> 00:11:30.770 align:middle line:90%
speak them out.

00:11:30.770 --> 00:11:33.990 align:middle line:84%
They'd all appear in rhyme
and meter, perfectly done.

00:11:33.990 --> 00:11:37.950 align:middle line:84%
And then when he came out, the
students would say, oh, my god.

00:11:37.950 --> 00:11:39.030 align:middle line:90%
That was tremendous.

00:11:39.030 --> 00:11:39.830 align:middle line:90%
Write that down.

00:11:39.830 --> 00:11:40.630 align:middle line:90%
No, he said.

00:11:40.630 --> 00:11:41.640 align:middle line:90%
No, let's keep dancing.

00:11:41.640 --> 00:11:42.490 align:middle line:90%
Let's go.

00:11:42.490 --> 00:11:43.290 align:middle line:90%
That's only words.

00:11:43.290 --> 00:11:56.460 align:middle line:90%


00:11:56.460 --> 00:11:59.310 align:middle line:84%
>>Rumi says that everything
is for the beloved.

00:11:59.310 --> 00:12:01.720 align:middle line:90%
Everything is for the friend.

00:12:01.720 --> 00:12:07.460 align:middle line:84%
And my understanding
of that is that there

00:12:07.460 --> 00:12:15.060 align:middle line:84%
is a presence that
we feel in the beauty

00:12:15.060 --> 00:12:17.600 align:middle line:90%
that we see outside of us.

00:12:17.600 --> 00:12:20.510 align:middle line:90%
We feel it in a November sunset.

00:12:20.510 --> 00:12:24.180 align:middle line:84%
We feel it in a child
sleeping, in a child dancing,

00:12:24.180 --> 00:12:25.450 align:middle line:90%
playing soccer.

00:12:25.450 --> 00:12:30.265 align:middle line:84%
We feel it in a group of friends
making supper on Sunday night.

00:12:30.265 --> 00:12:41.310 align:middle line:90%


00:12:41.310 --> 00:12:45.970 align:middle line:84%
He would say that feeling
is a presence that

00:12:45.970 --> 00:12:52.180 align:middle line:84%
is both outside of us and
tending us and inside us.

00:12:52.180 --> 00:12:55.090 align:middle line:84%
When we feel the
jewel-like quality

00:12:55.090 --> 00:12:59.680 align:middle line:84%
of our own inner awareness,
that also is the friend.

00:12:59.680 --> 00:13:06.500 align:middle line:84%
And this inner outer presence
is addressed directly

00:13:06.500 --> 00:13:08.020 align:middle line:90%
in many of Rumi's poems.

00:13:08.020 --> 00:13:25.090 align:middle line:90%


00:13:25.090 --> 00:13:28.250 align:middle line:84%
When he says that
wonderful pronoun "you"

00:13:28.250 --> 00:13:32.430 align:middle line:84%
and you don't quite know who
it is, it's that presence.

00:13:32.430 --> 00:13:37.950 align:middle line:84%
"When it's cold and raining," he
says, "you are more beautiful,

00:13:37.950 --> 00:13:43.610 align:middle line:84%
and the snow brings me
even closer to your lips.

00:13:43.610 --> 00:13:48.460 align:middle line:84%
The inner secret, that
which was never born.

00:13:48.460 --> 00:13:53.450 align:middle line:84%
You are that freshness,
and I am with you now.

00:13:53.450 --> 00:13:57.640 align:middle line:84%
I can't explain the
goings or the comings.

00:13:57.640 --> 00:14:02.420 align:middle line:84%
You enter suddenly,
and I am nowhere again,

00:14:02.420 --> 00:15:32.140 align:middle line:90%
inside the majesty."

00:15:32.140 --> 00:15:35.560 align:middle line:90%
"I. You.

00:15:35.560 --> 00:15:38.290 align:middle line:90%


00:15:38.290 --> 00:15:40.595 align:middle line:90%
He.

00:15:40.595 --> 00:15:41.395 align:middle line:90%
She.

00:15:41.395 --> 00:15:43.820 align:middle line:90%


00:15:43.820 --> 00:15:44.620 align:middle line:90%
We.

00:15:44.620 --> 00:15:48.480 align:middle line:90%


00:15:48.480 --> 00:15:53.210 align:middle line:84%
In the garden of
mystical lovers,

00:15:53.210 --> 00:15:59.343 align:middle line:90%
these are not true distinctions.

00:15:59.343 --> 00:16:02.060 align:middle line:90%


00:16:02.060 --> 00:16:05.427 align:middle line:90%
I. You.

00:16:05.427 --> 00:16:07.570 align:middle line:90%


00:16:07.570 --> 00:16:08.370 align:middle line:90%
He.

00:16:08.370 --> 00:16:11.080 align:middle line:90%


00:16:11.080 --> 00:16:13.770 align:middle line:90%
She.

00:16:13.770 --> 00:16:29.220 align:middle line:90%
We."

