00:49:25.880 --> 00:49:29.490 align:middle line:10%
And then for that, you pass
really every day with Rumi,

00:49:29.490 --> 00:49:31.140 align:middle line:10%
not once a day.

00:49:31.140 --> 00:49:32.890 align:middle line:90%
I pass now as well.

00:49:32.890 --> 00:49:39.130 align:middle line:84%
I pass maybe two hours, three
hours, like this with Rumi,

00:49:39.130 --> 00:49:42.030 align:middle line:90%
and I feel in paradise.

00:49:42.030 --> 00:49:43.840 align:middle line:90%
I fly with Rumi.

00:49:43.840 --> 00:49:46.610 align:middle line:90%
I go to the sky.

00:49:46.610 --> 00:49:49.195 align:middle line:84%
I will forget that
I'm on the earth.

00:49:49.195 --> 00:49:53.000 align:middle line:90%


00:49:53.000 --> 00:49:57.630 align:middle line:84%
>>He said, I go into
the Christian church,

00:49:57.630 --> 00:49:59.920 align:middle line:84%
and I go into the
Muslim mosque, and I

00:49:59.920 --> 00:50:04.890 align:middle line:84%
go into the Jewish synagogue,
and I see one altar.

00:50:04.890 --> 00:50:10.540 align:middle line:84%
He saw a single
impulse to worship

00:50:10.540 --> 00:50:13.960 align:middle line:90%
at the core of all religions.

00:50:13.960 --> 00:50:18.490 align:middle line:84%
When he died, members
of every faith in Konya

00:50:18.490 --> 00:50:22.950 align:middle line:84%
came to his funeral
honoring him,

00:50:22.950 --> 00:50:28.040 align:middle line:84%
as they felt a way of
deepening into their own faith.

00:50:28.040 --> 00:50:32.080 align:middle line:84%
>>That is the reason
everyone was there.

00:50:32.080 --> 00:50:37.490 align:middle line:84%
Maybe every nation, they
love their own prophets.

00:50:37.490 --> 00:50:42.800 align:middle line:84%
Every order, they
like their own sheiks.

00:50:42.800 --> 00:50:48.690 align:middle line:84%
But everyone loved
Mawlawi Jalal ad-Din Rumi.

00:50:48.690 --> 00:50:53.570 align:middle line:84%
>>He says, "I'm not Christian,
not Jew, not Muslim, not Hindu,

00:50:53.570 --> 00:50:55.355 align:middle line:90%
not Buddhist."

00:50:55.355 --> 00:50:58.300 align:middle line:84%
He says, "I belong
to the beloved.

00:50:58.300 --> 00:51:00.830 align:middle line:84%
I have seen the
two worlds as one,

00:51:00.830 --> 00:51:10.360 align:middle line:84%
and that one call to and know
first, last, outer, inner, only

00:51:10.360 --> 00:51:44.450 align:middle line:84%
that breath-breathing
human being."

00:51:44.450 --> 00:51:48.508 align:middle line:84%
"This we have now
is not imagination.

00:51:48.508 --> 00:51:52.340 align:middle line:90%


00:51:52.340 --> 00:51:59.200 align:middle line:84%
This is not grief or
joy, not a judging state

00:51:59.200 --> 00:52:04.640 align:middle line:90%
or an elation or a sadness.

00:52:04.640 --> 00:52:05.975 align:middle line:90%
Those come and go.

00:52:05.975 --> 00:52:09.440 align:middle line:90%


00:52:09.440 --> 00:52:12.400 align:middle line:84%
This is the presence
that doesn't.

00:52:12.400 --> 00:52:17.360 align:middle line:90%


00:52:17.360 --> 00:52:26.580 align:middle line:84%
It's dawn, Husam, here
in the splendor of coral,

00:52:26.580 --> 00:52:33.723 align:middle line:84%
inside the friend, in the simple
truth of what Hallaj said.

00:52:33.723 --> 00:52:37.180 align:middle line:90%


00:52:37.180 --> 00:52:38.840 align:middle line:84%
What else could
human beings want?

00:52:38.840 --> 00:52:42.050 align:middle line:90%


00:52:42.050 --> 00:52:46.251 align:middle line:84%
When grapes turn to wine,
they're wanting this.

00:52:46.251 --> 00:52:48.960 align:middle line:90%


00:52:48.960 --> 00:52:55.460 align:middle line:84%
When the night sky pours by,
it's really a crowd of beggars,

00:52:55.460 --> 00:52:57.073 align:middle line:90%
and they all want some of this.

00:52:57.073 --> 00:52:59.623 align:middle line:90%


00:52:59.623 --> 00:53:10.640 align:middle line:84%
This that we are now created
the body cell by cell,

00:53:10.640 --> 00:53:12.270 align:middle line:90%
like bees building a honeycomb.

00:53:12.270 --> 00:53:14.970 align:middle line:90%


00:53:14.970 --> 00:53:20.810 align:middle line:84%
The universe and the human
body grew from this, not this

00:53:20.810 --> 00:53:22.729 align:middle line:84%
from the universe
and the human body.

00:53:22.729 --> 00:53:26.950 align:middle line:90%


00:53:26.950 --> 00:53:31.195 align:middle line:84%
This that we have now
is not imagination.

00:53:31.195 --> 00:53:34.590 align:middle line:90%


00:53:34.590 --> 00:53:42.620 align:middle line:84%
This is not grief or
joy, not a judging state

00:53:42.620 --> 00:53:46.930 align:middle line:90%
or an elation or a sadness.

00:53:46.930 --> 00:53:50.300 align:middle line:90%
Those come and go.

00:53:50.300 --> 00:53:52.740 align:middle line:84%
This is the presence
that doesn't.

00:53:52.740 --> 00:53:57.490 align:middle line:90%


00:53:57.490 --> 00:53:58.310 align:middle line:90%
It's dawn, Husam.

00:53:58.310 --> 00:54:04.520 align:middle line:90%


00:54:04.520 --> 00:54:10.154 align:middle line:84%
What else could
human beings want?"

